I.name: Get Excited!
description: {{sbc|Innate:}} Whenever '''Jinx''' scores a {{tip|takedown}} against an enemy {{tip|champion}}, epic {{tip|monster}}, {{tip|turret}}, or [[inhibitor]] within 3 seconds of damaging them, she gains {{sti|ms|{{as|175% '''bonus''' movement speed}}}} which decays over 6 seconds.
Additionally, she gains {{sti|{{as|25% '''total''' attack speed}}}} and is allowed to exceed the {{tt|attack speed cap|normally 2.5 attacks per second}} for the same duration.
I.descriptionHtml:
Innate: Whenever Jinx scores a takedown against an enemy champion, epic monster, turret, or inhibitor within 3 seconds of damaging them, she gains 175% bonus movement speed which decays over 6 seconds.
Additionally, she gains 25% total attack speed and is allowed to exceed the attack speed cap for the same duration.

Q1.name: Switcheroo!
description: {{sbc|Toggle:}} '''Jinx''' switches between ''{{cci|Pow-Pow.png|Jinx#Pow-Pow|Pow-Pow}}'', her minigun, and ''{{cci|Fishbones.png|Jinx#Fishbones|Fishbones}}'', her rocket launcher.

{{sbc|Pow-Pow:}} Basic attacks with '''Pow-Pow''' generate a [[stack]] of [[File:Jinx Rev'd up.png|20px]] ''Rev'd up'' for {{fd|2.5}} seconds, stacking up to 3 times, with the duration refreshing on subsequent attacks with '''Pow-Pow'''. ''Rev'd up'' grants {{sti|{{as|'''bonus''' attack speed}}}}, with the first stack being twice as potent. Stacks expire one at a time.

{{sbc|Fishbones:}} Basic attacks with '''Fishbones''' cost {{sti|{{as|mana}}}} {{tip|on-attack}} to deal {{as|110% AD}} {{as|'''modified''' physical damage}} to the primary target as well as surrounding enemies. The damage is affected by {{tip|critical strike}} modifiers. While using '''Fishbones''',  '''Jinx''' gains {{sti|range|'''bonus''' range}} but loses {{sti|{{as|10% of her '''bonus''' attack speed}}}}.
Only the first attack after switching to '''Fishbones''' will benefit from ''Rev'd up''.
Q1.descriptionHtml:
Toggle: Jinx switches between Unknown value: cci / Pow-Pow.png / Jinx#Pow-Pow / Pow-Pow, her minigun, and Unknown value: cci / Fishbones.png / Jinx#Fishbones / Fishbones, her rocket launcher.
Pow-Pow: Basic attacks with Pow-Pow generate a stack of File:Jinx Rev'd up.png Rev'd up for 2.5 seconds, stacking up to 3 times, with the duration refreshing on subsequent attacks with Pow-Pow. Rev'd up grants bonus attack speed, with the first stack being twice as potent. Stacks expire one at a time.
Fishbones: Basic attacks with Fishbones cost mana on-attack to deal 110% AD modified physical damage to the primary target as well as surrounding enemies. The damage is affected by critical strike modifiers. While using Fishbones, Jinx gains bonus range but loses 10% of her bonus attack speed.
Only the first attack after switching to Fishbones will benefit from Rev'd up.
Q1.notes:
* Toggle abilities do not count as ability activations for the purposes of on-cast effects such as {{tip|Spellblade}} and stacking {{ai|Force Pulse|Kassadin}}.
* '''Jinx's''' first attack after switching to {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} can be triggered after {{fd|0.4}} seconds, instead of using the attack timer.
* Despite '''Jinx''' starting the game using {{ai|Pow-Pow|Jinx|''Pow-Pow''}} she doesn't receive any bonus attack speed until ''Switcheroo!'' has been learned.
* {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} splash damage affects structures (minions will target '''Jinx''') but does not affect targets if '''Jinx's''' attacks are {{tip|block|blocked}}, {{tip|dodge|dodged}}, or {{tip|blind|missed}}.
* With {{ii|Runaan's Hurricane}} {{ai|Pow-Pow|Jinx|''Pow-Pow''}} generates one stack per enemy hit.
* Each of {{iis|Runaan's Hurricane}} additional bolts apply {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|Fishbones'}} splash damage, which stacks with each other.
* Both weapons deal {{tip|basic damage}} to their primary target (this includes the increased damage of {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}}), which applies {{sti|life steal}} based on the damage dealt (post-mitigation) as usual.
* The splash damage of {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} is based on the pre-mitigation damage done to the primary target (which includes critical strikes), and is not considered {{as|'''modified''' physical damage}}. It deals {{tip|default damage}}: It doesn't apply {{sti|life steal}} or [[on-hit effect]]s.
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} damage: {{as|{{#expr:100+10}}% AD}} (100% + 10%).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} critical strike damage: {{as|{{fd|{{#expr:(100+10)*1.75}}}}% AD}} ((100% + 10%){{times}}{{fd|1.75}}).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} critical strike damage with {{ii|Infinity Edge}}: {{as|{{fd|{{#expr:(100+10)*2.1}}}}% AD}} ((100% + 10%){{times}}{{fd|2.1}}).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} {{ii|Runaan's Hurricane|bolt}} damage: {{as|{{#expr:(100+10)*0.4}}% AD}} ((100% + 10%){{times}}{{ii|Runaan's Hurricane|{{fd|0.4}}}}).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} {{ii|Runaan's Hurricane|bolt}} critical strike damage: {{as|{{fd|{{#expr:(100+10)*0.4*1.75}}}}% AD}} ((100% + 10%){{times}}{{ii|Runaan's Hurricane|{{fd|0.4}}}}{{times}}{{fd|1.75}}).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} {{ii|Runaan's Hurricane|bolt}} critical strike damage with {{ii|Infinity Edge}}: {{as|{{fd|{{#expr:(100+10)*0.4*2.1}}}}% AD}} ((100% + 10%){{times}}{{ii|Runaan's Hurricane|{{fd|0.4}}}}{{times}}{{fd|2.1}}).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} potential damage on stacked enemies with {{ii|Runaan's Hurricane}}: {{as|{{fd|{{#expr:(100+10)+(100+10)*0.4*2}}}}% AD}} (110% + 44% + 44%).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} potential critical strike damage on stacked enemies with {{ii|Runaan's Hurricane}}: {{as|{{fd|{{#expr:((100+10)+(100+10)*0.4*2)*1.75}}}}% AD}} ((110% + 44% + 44%){{times}}{{fd|1.75}}).
** {{ai|Fishbones|Jinx|''Fishbones''}} potential critical strike damage on stacked enemies with {{ii|Runaan's Hurricane}} and {{ii|Infinity Edge}}: {{as|{{fd|{{#expr:((100+10)+(100+10)*0.4*2)*2.1}}}}% AD}} ((110% + 44% + 44%){{times}}{{fd|2.1}}).

W.name: Zap!
description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Jinx''' fires a shock blast in the target direction that deals {{as|physical damage}} to the first enemy it hits and {{tip|standard sight|reveals}} and {{tip|slow|slows}} them for 2 seconds.
W.descriptionHtml: Active: Jinx fires a shock blast in the target direction that deals physical damage to the first enemy it hits and reveals and slows them for 2 seconds.

E1.name: Flame Chompers!
description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Jinx''' tosses out 3 ''Chompers'' at the target location that land in a perpendicular line after {{fd|0.4}} seconds, arming after {{fd|0.5}} seconds, and exploding after 5 seconds, dealing {{as|magic damage}} to all enemies within a small area.

Each ''Chomper'' explodes on contact with an enemy {{tip|champion|champion}}, {{tip|knockdown|knocking them down}} and {{tip|root|rooting}} them for {{fd|1.5}} seconds. Enemy champions can only be affected by one ''Chomper''.
''Flame Chompers! will cast at max range if cast beyond that.''
E1.descriptionHtml:
Active: Jinx tosses out 3 Chompers at the target location that land in a perpendicular line after 0.4 seconds, arming after 0.5 seconds, and exploding after 5 seconds, dealing magic damage to all enemies within a small area.
Each Chomper explodes on contact with an enemy champion, knocking them down and rooting them for 1.5 seconds. Enemy champions can only be affected by one Chomper.
Flame Chompers! will cast at max range if cast beyond that.
E1.notes:
* ''Chompers'' will halt when encountering {{ai|Wind Wall|Yasuo}} and {{ai|Unbreakable|Braum}}.
* {{tip|Spell shield}} does not negate the explosion.

R.name: Super Mega Death Rocket!
description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Jinx''' fires a rocket in the target direction, granting brief {{tip|sight}} of the {{tt|area|Cannot grant sight into brush nor through terrain}} it flies through. The rocket explodes upon colliding with an enemy champion, dealing {{as|physical damage}} to them and all enemies in an {{tt|area|centered on the initial target}} around them and granting {{tip|sight}} of the {{tt|area|Can grant sight into brush and through terrain}} around them for 2 seconds.
The rocket deals {{pp|type=distance traveled|key=%|10 to 100 for 16|0 to 1500}} damage; the '''bonus''' damage based on {{as|'''missing''' health}} is kept the same.

Enemies surrounding the main target take 80% damage. '''Bonus''' damage based on {{as|'''missing''' health}} is based on each unit's own {{as|'''missing''' health}}, with a maximum '''bonus''' damage of 800 against {{tip|monsters}}.
